The paper discusses topics related to formal verification, automata theory, and logics, which are all subfields of theoretical computer science. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also covers game theory and software verification, which are relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SE (Software Engineering), respectively. Additionally, the paper mentions hybrid systems, which are studied in cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
